A series of terror attacks in Jaipur, India, killed over 80 people and injured 200.
The bombings, condemned by global leaders, sparked fears of escalating violence.
Authorities suspect Pakistan-based militant groups.
The historic city, known for its palaces, faced devastation as bombs tore through markets and temples.
The international community expressed solidarity with India in combating terrorism.
The tragic events underscore the ongoing threat of indiscriminate violence.
The government issued a nationwide security alert, emphasizing the need for unity and calm in the face of such senseless acts.
The toll of casualties continues to rise, highlighting the urgent need for vigilance and cooperation in combating terrorism.
